VALUES
(40, 9, 25, 42, 8, 54, 54, 'took her by the hand', 'Healing of the Maid', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus taking the maid by the hand and commanding her to arise. This connection highlights the miraculous healing performed by Jesus in similar circumstances.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 25, 12, 4, 32, 36, 'the maid arose', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the act of raising the dead. In Matthew, Jesus takes the girl by the hand and she arises, while in 2 Kings, Elisha stretches himself upon the child and brings him back to life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 25, 44, 9, 40, 41, 'took her by the hand', 'Resurrection Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the act of raising someone from the dead. In Matthew, Jesus takes the maid by the hand, while in Acts, Peter says, ''Tabitha, arise,'' and then lifts her up.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 26, 40, 4, 24, 24, NULL, 'Connection of Fame in Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the spread of Jesus'' fame due to his healing miracles. In Matthew 4:24, his fame leads to many bringing sick people to him, while Matthew 9:26 notes that his fame went abroad into all the land.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 26, 40, 14, 1, 2, 'the fame hereof went abroad', 'Connection of Fame of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the spread of Jesus'' fame, as noted in both passages. The mention of ''fame'' in Matthew 9:26 directly relates to Herod''s awareness of Jesus'' reputation in Matthew 14:1-2.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 26, 41, 1, 45, 45, 'the fame hereof went abroad', 'Spread of Jesus'' Fame', 'Both passages emphasize the widespread fame of Jesus following his miracles. In Matthew, the fame ''went abroad into all that land,'' while in Mark, the man ''began to publish it much,'' leading to Jesus being sought after from various places.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 26, 41, 6, 14, 14, 'fame hereof went abroad', 'Spread of Fame and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of fame surrounding Jesus and John the Baptist. Both passages emphasize how their names and deeds were widely known, leading to significant recognition and speculation about their identities.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 26, 44, 26, 26, 26, 'the fame hereof went abroad', 'Public Awareness of Events', 'This connection highlights the public nature of significant events in both passages. Matthew notes that ''the fame hereof went abroad,'' while Acts emphasizes that ''none of these things are hidden from him,'' suggesting widespread knowledge of miraculous occurrences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 40, 15, 22, 22, 'Thou Son of David, have mercy on us.', 'Connection of Mercy and Son of David', 'Both passages emphasize the plea for mercy directed to Jesus as the ''Son of David.'' This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' messianic identity by individuals in need of healing.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 40, 20, 30, 31, 'Thou Son of David, have mercy on us', 'Blind Men Seeking Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the plea for mercy from blind men who recognize Jesus as the ''Son of David.'' This connection highlights the consistent theme of faith and desperation in seeking healing from Jesus.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 41, 10, 46, 48, 'Thou Son of David, have mercy on us', 'Blindness and Mercy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the plea for mercy from Jesus by blind individuals who recognize him as the ''Son of David.'' This connection highlights the theme of faith and desperation in seeking healing.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 42, 18, 38, 39, 'Thou Son of David, have mercy on us', 'Connection of Blindness and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the plea for mercy from Jesus by individuals who identify him as the ''Son of David.'' This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' messianic title and the theme of healing for the blind.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 41, 9, 22, 22, 'have mercy on us', 'Compassion and Mercy in Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the plea for compassion and help in times of distress. The phrase ''have mercy on us'' in Matthew parallels the request for compassion in Mark, highlighting a common theme of seeking divine assistance.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 42, 7, 21, 21, 'have mercy on us', 'Healing of the Blind', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of blindness, with Matthew highlighting the plea for mercy from the blind men and Luke noting Jesus curing many blind individuals. This connection highlights the compassionate response of Jesus to those in need of sight.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 27, 43, 7, 42, 42, 'Thou Son of David', 'Connection of David''s Lineage', 'This connection highlights the acknowledgment of Jesus as the ''Son of David'' by the blind men, linking him to the messianic expectation rooted in David''s lineage. Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus'' descent from David, fulfilling the scriptural prophecy regarding the Messiah''s origins.', 'prophecy', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 28, 41, 9, 23, 24, 'Believe ye that I am able to do this?', 'Connection of Belief and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of belief for healing. In Matthew, the blind men affirm their belief in Jesus'' ability, while in Mark, the father expresses his belief and seeks help for his doubt.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 28, 40, 8, 2, 2, 'Yea, Lord', 'Faith in Jesus'' Healing Power', 'Both passages emphasize the faith of individuals seeking healing from Jesus. The blind men affirm their belief in his ability, while the leper expresses hope in his willingness to heal.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 28, 40, 9, 22, 22, 'Believe ye that I am able to do this?', 'Connection of Faith and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew 9:28, the blind men affirm their belief in Jesus'' ability, while in Matthew 9:22, the woman''s faith is credited for her healing.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 28, 43, 11, 26, 26, 'Believe ye that I am able to do this?', 'Faith in Jesus'' Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus'' ability to grant life and healing. Both passages emphasize the necessity of faith in Jesus for receiving His power, whether for physical sight or eternal life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 28, 43, 11, 40, 40, 'Believe ye that I am able to do this?', 'Connection of Belief and Sight', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in witnessing divine acts. In Matthew, belief precedes the healing of the blind men, while in John, belief is linked to seeing God''s glory.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 40, 15, 28, 28, 'According to your faith be it unto you', 'Connection of Faith and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew 9:29, Jesus states, ''According to your faith be it unto you,'' while in Matthew 15:28, he acknowledges, ''great is thy faith'' and grants her request for healing.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 41, 10, 52, 52, NULL, 'Faith and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew, Jesus states, ''According to your faith be it unto you,'' while in Mark, he declares, ''thy faith hath made thee whole.'' This highlights the direct link between faith and the restoration of sight.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 40, 8, 13, 13, 'According to your faith be it unto you', 'Faith and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew 9:29, Jesus states, ''According to your faith be it unto you,'' while in Matthew 8:13, he says, ''as thou hast believed, so be it done unto thee.'' This connection highlights the importance of belief in receiving healing.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 40, 9, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Faith and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew 9:29, Jesus states, ''According to your faith be it unto you,'' while in Matthew 9:22, he tells the woman, ''thy faith hath made thee whole.'' This connection highlights how faith is a crucial element in the miracles performed by Jesus.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 40, 20, 34, 34, NULL, 'Healing Through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus touching the eyes of the blind, resulting in restored sight. The phrase ''touched their eyes'' in Matthew 20:34 connects directly to the healing context established in Matthew 9:29, where faith plays a crucial role in the healing process.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 29, 43, 9, 6, 7, 'According to your faith be it unto you', 'Faith and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in healing. In Matthew, Jesus states, ''According to your faith be it unto you,'' while in John, the blind man''s healing follows his obedience to Jesus'' command, suggesting a link between faith and miraculous sight.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 30, 40, 8, 4, 4, 'See that no man know it', 'Instructions to Silence', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus instructing individuals not to tell others about their healing. This connection highlights a recurring theme of secrecy surrounding Jesus'' miracles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 30, 42, 5, 14, 14, NULL, 'Instructions to Silence', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus charging individuals to tell no one about their miraculous healings. This connection highlights a theme of secrecy surrounding Jesus'' miracles and the importance of following his commands.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 30, 40, 12, 16, 16, NULL, 'Jesus'' Charge for Silence', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' instruction to keep his identity concealed. In Matthew 9:30, he charges them to not let anyone know, and in Matthew 12:16, he similarly instructs them not to make him known.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 30, 41, 5, 43, 43, NULL, 'Commands to Keep Secrets', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' instruction to keep his miracles confidential. This connection highlights a recurring theme of secrecy surrounding his works.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
